What do you think they have, other than the IP address he used today? A TCP/IP packet does not contain a video of the guy who sends it saying "My name is Shitbag Retard and I live at 1313 Mockingbird Lane, Cucamonga, California." From an IP address you can say "this guy is a customer of such-and-such ISP and if we understand how they assign blocks of IP addresses correctly we think he might be somewhere in the eastern half of Texas." If he was using a VPN or TOR you don't even get that much information.

There are ways and means but I very strongly doubt that volunteer mods on a Taiwanese stamp collecting forum are going to have them. Yeah, if someone starts flooding CP, and the mods go to law enforcement, the matter might eventually get onto the desk of someone at the FBI. And the FBI can take that IP address and a warrant and go to the ISP and say "on such-and-such date this IP address was used for illegal traffic. Which of your customers was it?" Short of that, something very unusual would have to have happened. Like, maybe somewhere our friend--for purposes of this discussion, let's call him "Fucknozzle"--is posting screenshots of himself spamming here on Facebook, or whatever. And maybe he thinks that account is safe and pseudo-anonymous in the sense that he signed up for it with phony information and an email address that he thinks isn't linked to his regular one. And we all just learned that Gab was a big ol' honeypot (Heavy Weapons Guy voice: "not beeg surprise") and people who put their personal information in it and linked Gab accounts got their dox made public. And maybe someone who really has a hateboner for Fucknozzle cares enough to search out his Facebook account then search through the publicized Gab data for matches. But that requires a number of things to have happened just perfectly so.
